  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 - \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb9\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The solution to the country's problems from the end of July - Minister Harin hopes",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Tourism Minister Harin Fernando said he hoped to gradually recover from the problems by the end of July through programs implemented by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "He was speaking at a press conference at the Ministry of Tourism (27) on Monday.",
        "We will disclose to the country soon the issues discussed with the International Monetary Fund.",
        "The continued blaming of the country by some, including politicians, has had a severe impact on tourism. We therefore urge everyone not to engage in such activities.",
        "Many are now urging Ranil Wickremesinghe to resign. Who is qualified to deal with these crises if he resigns? Those who refused to accept responsibility when it was granted speak out against it today.",
        "They say the country is now ready to take responsibility. Individuals with desire and fear say, 'The dog does not eat. Do not feed the eater '.",
        "However, we are confident that the problems in the country will begin to ease by the end of July.",
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe has given us that promise. Opposition leader Sajid Premadasa has been campaigning for the people to take to the streets in this situation. Is it possible to solve problems in a day or two just by fighting in the streets like this?",
        "Sajid says we have gone to Gotabhaya Rajapaksa. But we do know how he was going to go to Gotabhaya Rajapaksa on which occasions.",
        "Due to the fact that our party did not co-operate in rescuing the country from the crisis situation, we decided to accept the ministry responsibilities for the benefit of the people of the country.",
        "We are still a united people today. Many saw the need to expel us from the party.",
        "But the United People's Power is not Sajid Premadasa's party. He is only its leader. So he can not remove us from the party. Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe has implemented a number of important programs. Based on that, we expect to be able to gradually recover from the problems by the end of next month."
      ],
